resources.string:
String - stores text, such as "HelloWorld". Double quotes are used to enclose string values.
Ex. String myText = "Hello";

int - stores integers or whole numbers, without decimals, such as 246 or -246.
Ex.int myNum = 5;

float - stores floating point numbers, with decimals, such as 3.99 or -3.99.
Ex. float myFloatNum = 5.99f;

char - stores single characters, such as 'a' or 'B'. Single quotes are used to enclose char values.
Ex char myLetter = 'D';

boolean - stores values with two states: true or false.
Ex. boolean myBoolean = true;

