Example: 
 int count = 1; 
 while (count <= 5) { 
 	System.out.println("Count: " + count);
 	count++; 
 }

 Output: 
 Count: 1 
 Count: 2 
 Count: 3 
 Count: 4 
 Count: 5 

 Example explained: 
 the while loop starts with the condition count <= 5. The loop body will execute as long as the condition is true. Inside the loop, the current value of count is printed using System.out.println(), and then count is incremented by 1 (count++). This ensures that the loop will eventually terminate when count becomes greater than 5.

